From 3e6f7946c959bd62d1779b95ed8c81622e4f6293 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Date: Thu, 29 Jan 2026 15:23:17 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] docs: user_guide: improve IP settings without Network
 Manager

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific]
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
---
 docs/user_guide/setup.md | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/docs/user_guide/setup.md b/docs/user_guide/setup.md
index b24d29c..03a18e6 100644
--- a/docs/user_guide/setup.md
+++ b/docs/user_guide/setup.md
@@ -480,6 +480,8 @@ which is the RJ45 connector on the AGX Orin.
 
 - Enable the network interface and ensure that the camera enumerates (assumes camera IP address 192.168.0.2):
 
+  - with Network Manager:
+
   ```none
   EN0=mgbe0_0
   sudo nmcli con add con-name hololink-$EN0 ifname $EN0 type ethernet ip4 192.168.0.101/24
@@ -487,6 +489,15 @@ which is the RJ45 connector on the AGX Orin.
   sudo nmcli connection up hololink-$EN0
   ```
 
+  - Without Network manager
+
+  ```none
+  EN0=mgbe0_0
+  sudo ip link set dev $EN0 up
+  sudo ip addr add 192.168.0.101/24 dev $EN0
+  sudo ip route add 192.168.0.2/32 dev $EN0
+  ```
+
 - Obtain and build holoscan sensor bridge:
 
   holoscan sensor bridge release v2.5 supports running C++ Li VB1940 accelerated networking [SIPL](https://docs.nvidia.com/jetson/archives/r38.2.1/DeveloperGuide/SD/CameraDevelopment/CoECameraDevelopment/SIPL-for-L4T/Introduction-to-SIPL.html) based examples 
